## Law Constraints Reference (verbatim, for traceability)

```
1. Distance Between Work-Free Weekends
   At minimum every 5 weeks, one work-free weekend (entire Saturday and Sunday) must be allocated.
   Vacation time replaces work-free weekend allocation if it includes complete weekends.

4. Rest Time Between Shifts
   A person must have a minimum of 12 hours of rest time between shifts.

6. Rest Days
   A person must have a minimum of 4 Rest-Days (RT) and 2 Compensation Days (CT),
   so in total a minimum of 6 days of rest in a month.
   See 1.): A person must have minimum of 1 weekend each Month as Rest Days
   (Saturday and Sunday concurrent). Between these Rest Weekends there must not
   be a gap of more than 5 Weeks.
```

