## Decision Summary (from review session)

| # | Topic | Decision |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Approach | HARD constraint (CP-SAT decision variables), NOT post-processing |
| 2 | Day-level vs interval | Day-level Boolean decision variables `rt[r,d]`, `ct[r,d]` |
| 3 | Anchor (start time) | `[shift_end_prev, shift_end_prev + 24h]` — naturally yields 12-12 / 13-13; falls back to midnight when no prior shift or > 24h away |
| 4 | Per-month vs window | Calendar-month decomposition **always** (no short-range bypass); `ceil` rounding for partial months |
| 5 | Combined target | `≥6` rest days (RT+CT combined) per full month or prorated segment |
| 6 | Weekend rest | Reuse LC-05 hard constraint (sliding 5-week window); couple its `free_weekend_vars` to RT/CT to mark Sat+Sun as RT/CT |
| 7 | Output A | JSONB `planner_output.assignments` includes CT/RT objects with `assignment_type` |
| 8 | Output B | `planner_assignments` table includes CT/RT rows with `assignment_type`, `request_id=NULL` |
| 9 | `request_id` | **NULLABLE** for CT/RT (no demand exists); DEMAND rows unchanged |
| 10 | Output flags | `fetch_rt`, `fetch_ct` BOOLEAN on `planner_output` (FE-driven decision: re-fetch from external DB or read solver output) |
| 11 | Non-replannable case | No solver change; analyzer post-processing alert if external data violates 4 RT + 2 CT |
| 12 | Other 7 absence types | Stay protected by `sanitize_replannable_types()` — never replannable |
| 13 | LC-08 v2 gating | LC-08 v2 is actively enforced (`config.py:198`). Gate: skip when LC-06 active; keep as fallback otherwise |
| 14 | Missing carryover | Graceful degradation: log warning, use full prorated targets per segment |
| 15 | Cross-partition weekends | `free_weekend_by_month` in `ResourceState` for LC-06 weekend injection |
| 16 | Month decomposition | Always decompose by month; no "< 5 weeks → single target" shortcut |
| 17 | Anchor at partition boundary | Check `partition_state.last_shift_end` first; midnight fallback only if absent or > 24h |

